**Summary:**

The story centers on Mira, a girl with the ability to communicate with trees. After a small fire is contained, Mira begins receiving urgent warnings from an ancient tree named Grandfather Cedar. The messages reveal a "sickness" spreading through the roots, which Mira interprets as a warning of an impending fire. Despite the rangers dismissing the threat due to the wet season, Mira and the village children attempt to heal the tree with a sap mixture. As summer brings dry heat, Mira rushes to the ranger station to warn them that the forest is "afraid," but smoke begins to rise.